io.hekate.metrics.cloudwatch

Class CloudWatchMetricsPlugin

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.hekate.metrics.cloudwatch.CloudWatchMetricsPlugin
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Plugin

    public class CloudWatchMetricsPlugin
extends Object
implements Plugin
    « start hereAmazon CloudWatch metrics publisher plugin.

    Overview

    This plugin provides support for publishing metrics from LocalMetricsService to Amazon CloudWatch.

    Metrics are asynchronously published once per CloudWatchMetricsConfig.setPublishInterval(int) interval as StatisticSets. Each StatisticSet contains average values that were aggregated during that interval.

    Important! Publishing metrics the Amazon CloudWatch service requires cloudwatch:PutMetricData permission to be set for the EC2 instance's IAM role.

    Module Dependency

    CloudWatch support is provided by the 'hekate-metrics-cloudwatch' module and can be imported into the project dependency management system as in the example below:

    • Maven
    • Gradle
    • Ivy
    
 <dependency>
   <groupId>io.hekate</groupId>
   <artifactId>hekate-metrics-cloudwatch</artifactId>
   <version>2.4.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
 </dependency>
 
    
 compile group: 'io.hekate', name: 'hekate-metrics-cloudwatch', version: '2.4.0-SNAPSHOT'
 
    
 <dependency org="io.hekate" name="hekate-metrics-cloudwatch" rev="2.4.0-SNAPSHOT"/>

    Configuration

    Configuration options of this plugin are represented by the CloudWatchMetricsConfig class. Please see the documentation of its properties for more details.

    Registering Plugin

    This plugin can be registered via HekateBootstrap.setPlugins(List) method as in the example below:

    1) Prepare plugin configuration. 

    
CloudWatchMetricsConfig cloudWatchCfg = new CloudWatchMetricsConfig()
    // Publishing interval in seconds
    .withPublishInterval(60)
    // AWS credentials (optional when running with a EC2 instance).
    .withRegion("eu-central-1")
    .withAccessKey("<my access key>")
    .withSecretKey("<my secret key>");

    2) Register the plugin and start a new node. 

    
Hekate node = new HekateBootstrap()
    .withPlugin(new CloudWatchMetricsPlugin(cloudWatchCfg))
    .join();

    Metrics Names and Dimensions

    Metric names are converted to camel case. For example, if metric name is jvm.mem.used then it will be published as JvmMemUsed

    During publishing each metric gets tagged with the following dimensions:

    • NodeName - Name of a publisher node (see ClusterNode.name())
    • InstanceId - EC2 instance ID

    Metrics Filtering

    It is possible to filter out metrics that should not be published to CloudWatch by registering an instance of MetricFilter interface. Only those metrics that do match the specified filter will be published to CloudWatch.

    See Also:
    CloudWatchMetricsConfig, HekateBootstrap.setPlugins(List)
